This paper deals with game theory and decision making in the context of uncertain and bounded rationality agents, which are common topics in the sub-fields of game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed approach on a real-world dataset, which falls under the sub-field of social informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which is a topic in the sub-field of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
